    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date: April 30, 2026</strong></p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Acoustic Mapper for Audiophiles</strong> handles information. Our core philosophy is "Privacy by Design," meaning we believe your data belongs to you.</p>

    <h2>1. Information Collection and Use</h2>
    <p>We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. "Acoustic Mapper for Audiophiles" is designed to function entirely offline. We do not use any third-party analytics or tracking software. No data regarding your identity, location, or usage habits is ever sent to us or any third party.</p>

    <h2>2. LiDAR and Sensor Data</h2>
    <p>Our app utilizes <strong>LiDAR (Light Detection and Ranging)</strong> technology to create 3D maps of your environment to calculate acoustic reflections and optimal speaker placement. </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Local Processing:</strong> All spatial data and depth maps generated by the LiDAR sensor are processed locally on your device in real-time.</li>
        <li><strong>No Storage:</strong> This data is used solely for the active calculation session. We do not store room maps on your device after the session is closed, nor do we upload this data to any servers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We do not integrate with any third-party services, social media platforms, or advertising networks. There are no external frameworks within the app that collect your information.</p>

    <h2>4. Security</h2>
    <p>Since the app does not collect or transmit data, there is no risk of your personal information being intercepted or leaked from our systems. We recommend keeping your iOS device updated to ensure the latest system-level security protections.</p>

    <h2>5. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this page. Since we do not collect contact information, we encourage users to check this page periodically for updates.</p>

